                            <Heading/>
                            <Paragraph>The Panel, created by act of April 29, 1968 (28
                                        U.S.C. 1407), and consisting of seven Federal judges
                                        designated by the Chief Justice from the courts of appeals
                                        and district courts, is authorized to temporarily transfer
                                        to a single district, for coordinated or consolidated
                                        pretrial proceedings, civil actions pending in different
                                        districts that involve one or more common questions of
                                        fact.</Paragraph>
                        </Detail>
                    </Details>
                </Activity>
